The paper discusses the use of genetic algorithms and artificial immune systems for behavior-based robotics, specifically for mobile robot navigation. This topic falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of networks and encoding of behaviors, which could fall under systems and control (cs.SY). The use of genetic algorithms and neural networks also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) or machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
